data.subject: ComfyUI-Q-Align
data.question: What is ComfyUI-Q-Align and where is it implemented from?
data.answer: ComfyUI-Q-Align is an unofficial implementation of Q-Align for ComfyUI, which is taken from the original Q-Align project available on GitHub.

data.subject: ComfyUI-Q-Align
data.question: What hardware requirements are needed to run ComfyUI-Q-Align?
data.answer: To run ComfyUI-Q-Align, you need a VRAM greater than 16GB.

data.subject: ComfyUI-Q-Align
data.question: Is ComfyUI-Q-Align an official feature of ComfyUI?
data.answer: No, ComfyUI-Q-Align is an unofficial implementation, meaning it is not an official feature of ComfyUI.
